hwater Aquarium or Saltwater Aquariums?  I had a Freshwater one before the 94 Northridge Earthquake.  (Can you guess what happened to it? <img border=0 src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/frown.gif" /> )  <br>
<br>
Anyways.  My question is more for the Saltwater people out there.  Should I give Saltwater a try or go back to Freshwater for a year or so and then try to upgrade my aquarium?  From what I have read, Saltwater is a lot of work and money.  If anyone has pointers on what type of fish to get and stuff, I'll be a very happy gnome.  I don't want to go into Saltwater and lose a ton of money <img border=0 src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif" /><br>
<br>
P.S. I just got a 30 gallon Tank tonight.  During the week I will get some decorations for the tank.  <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"> <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=170064"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.sc2k.org/images/sigpics/vita_evilundead1.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub134.ezboard.com/btabularasa19500.showUserPublicProfile?gid=evilundeadafterlife>Evilundead Afterlife</A> at: 1/11/04 11:24 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#242422><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub134.ezboard.com/btabularasa19500.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ballzz>Ballzz</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table style='Filter: Glow(Color=#FFFFFF,strength=4)'><tr><td><span class='usertitle'><font color=#000000><b> Got Cybor? </span></font></td></tr></TABLE></b></span><br>  Posts: 8505<br> <font color=#9999FF>(1/12/04 12:56 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p197.ezboard.com/ftabularasa19500frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3142.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.austin.rr.com/cproler/Ballzzface2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Freshwater Aquarium or Saltwater</span><hr size=1> I used to really be into the fish thing. I had a nice 50 gallon tank and always had freshwater. Saltwater is much more work and money. The fish are generally much more expensive and prone to die (mostly cuz it's so much work to keep the tank balance just right). No doubt saltlwater is much cooler if you get it going but be prepared to spend much more cash. <br>
<br>
I always got African Cichlids (pronounced siklid) for fish mostly. They are usually very colorful and some of them actually would change colors quite dramatically as they got older which was cool. They are also very aggressive and territorial so sometimes would fight with each other for space in the tank. <br>
<br>
I also usually had Tiger Oscars. These fish grew to get kinda big so would have to sometimes trade them back into the fish store (they give cash for the large ones...was much more than the baby ones cost). They are generally mellow and sort of float around a lot but can be aggressive at times. Generally, I was told they are not a good tankmate of the cichlid but I liked having a couple Oscars in with my cichlids. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
