Then start with reasonable fish. DAMSELS come in all colors and are like cockroaches...very tough to kill. Once u get comfortable u can move into anything. I have a marine betta in my tank right now and hes doing great.. btw in a year i have only done 1 partial water change.<br>
THEY ARE NOT TOUGH ANYMORE.  talk to someone at a fish specialty store and they will make it simple. although i do suggest a protein skimmer  but they are easy now also  they just sit in the underground sump.<br>
