I know little to nothing about fresh water but i would think the circulation achieved in a reef ready tank would also be beneficial to fresh water.<br>
So i guess my answer is as would be on most topics if u go with the state of the art stuff it will be more expensive but im not sure that there would be a difference between salt or fresh water.<br>
To answer the question i have around $1600 in my tank, but in a year i have only lost 3 fish and keep my tank well stocked. I currently have 14 fish,1 starfish and 4 snaills ( we do lose snails every now and then), 2 crabs, 2 shrimp, all in a 58 gallon tank.<br>
